  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A letter to the President from 80 MPs protesting Article 22",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to the report, nearly eighty members of Parliament have signed a petition and handed it over to the President, not to participate in the voting on the bill, if the clause that empowers the President to dissolve the Parliament in two and a half years, which has been included in the twenty-second constitutional amendment, is not amended.",
        "Thus, the group of MPs signing the petition includes a group of MPs from the Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna and a group of independent MPs from the opposition and parliament.",
        "By signing the petition, these MPs demand that the clause empowering the President to dissolve Parliament after two and a half years should be changed to four and a half years.",
        "Meanwhile, there has been a tug of war between the members of the government regarding the clause on the power assigned to the president to dissolve the parliament in two and a half years, which was included in the twenty-second constitutional amendment.",
        "Dissolution of Parliament in two and a half years is a clause included in the 20th Constitutional Amendment.",
        "The 22nd Constitution Amendment Bill was recently submitted to the Parliament by the Minister of Justice Dr. Vijayadasa Rajapaksa.",
        "The bill will soon be debated and passed."
      ],
